        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 8 at 7:34PM CDT until July 8 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 733 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles southeast of
Wellington, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible. Hail
damage to vehicles is expected.

Locations impacted include...
Dodson.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
